Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Composer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-7)

The Library is a key feature located in the right-side panel under the Insertion Points tab. Its primary function is to offer users access to a comprehensive list of building blocks, which are typically organized by template part packages. The Library allows users to efficiently locate, preview, and drag-and-drop these building blocks into their documents. Users can also navigate through nested folders and back up to the root folder of the Library.

The root folder is defined by the building-blocks property on the page-sequences ITX element. This property should be pre-defined in the template or can already be a part of the Composer document. The value of this property can be:

- A path relative to the ICR root, such as */my-folder/my-templates/library*.

- A path relative to the current template or document location, such as *../../my-library*.

- A path relative to the current project folder, such as *~project~/my-library*.

> Absolute paths pointing to random servers are not supported.

## Available Tab
The Available Tab is displayed only when the library root folder is correctly defined in the template or document and is valid. If not, only the Favourites Tab is rendered.

The Available Tab section enables users to filter the current list or groups of building blocks, or initiate a real server-side recursive search. This recursive search operates based on the building block name within the current and all nested sub-folders of the current library folder.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Library available tab*

Users can also toggle between rendering template part packages and a plain list of available building blocks. Each building block includes a preview icon and an icon to add or remove it from the list of favourites. The preview feature attempts to display a popup dialog with the pre-rendered content of the building block, showing how it would appear when dragged and dropped into the document. Users are notified if the preview fails or if there is no content to render.

A key feature of the Available Tab is the breadcrumbs navigator, which dynamically updates based on the current location. This navigator allows users to click on specific library folders or nested folders to navigate to any higher level of the library folders up to the root folder. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Library breadcrumbs*

## Favourites Tab
The Favourites Tab provides users with access to a personalized list of building blocks marked as favourites in the Available Tab. This section also allows filtering by building block name and offers the ability to preview the building blocks pre-rendered content. To remove a building block from the list of favourites, users simply click on the dark star icon.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Library favourites tab*

## Additional Features
The entire Library section is undock-able, allowing it to be used as a standalone window, similar to other sections. This flexibility enhances the user experience by enabling a more customized and efficient workflow.

Overall, the Library is designed to streamline the process of managing and utilizing custom components and template parts. It provides a robust and user-friendly interface for efficient design and development.
